        <updateDate>2005-08-11T19:18:33Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Zero Tolerance School Terror Act - Amends the federal criminal code to provide for a maximum penalty of 20 years' imprisonment for threatening to kill, injure, or intimidate an individual, or to cause property damage, by means of fire or an explosive on school property.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
